y Fair''\n|[[Anton Schwarzkopf|Schwarzkopf]]\n|Bayern Kurve\n|align=center|1976\n|-\n|Celebration Swings\n|''Celebration Plaza''\n|[[Zierer]]\n|[[Wave Swinger]]\n|align=center|2001\n|-\n|Centrifuge\n|''Action Zone''\n|[[Anton Schwarzkopf|Schwarzkopf]]\n|Calypso\n|align=center|1976\n|-\n|Delirium\n|''All American Corners''\n|Chance Rides\n|Revolution 32\n|align=center|2002\n|-\n|[[Drop Tower: Scream Zone]]\n|''Action Zone''\n|[[Intamin]]\n|Giant Drop\n|align=center|1996\n|-\n|Orbit\n|''All American Corners''\n|[[Anton Schwarzkopf|Schwarzkopf]]\n|[[Enterprise (ride)|Enterprise]]\n|align=center|1976\n|-\n|Tiki Twirl\n|''Action Zone''\n|[[Zamperla]]\n|Disk'O Coaster\n|align=center|2006\n|-\n|}\n\n===Action Zone===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Ride\n!Opened\n!Manufacturer, type\n!Notes\n!Rating<ref name=Rating/>\n|-\n|Centrifuge\n|1976\n|Schwarzkopf<br/>Calypso\n|Originally known as ''Fiddler's Fling''. Its Six Flags counterpart retains that name as of today.\n|bgcolor=\"#FFA343\" align=center | 3\n|-\n|[[Drop Tower: Scream Zone]]\n|1996\n|[[Intamin]]<br />Giant Drop\n|227 foot tall tower where riders descend at speeds up to 62&nbsp;mph (100&nbsp;km/h) while free falling in cars that hold up to four passengers. Originally known as ''Drop Zone: Stunt Tower'' from 1996\u20132007.\n|bgcolor=\"#FF0000\" align=center | 4\n|-\n|Eagle's Flight\n|1976\n|[[Von Roll]]<br />Gondola lift\n|''Eagle's Flight'' is the name for the Action Zone gondola station\n|bgcolor=\"#FFFF00\" align=center | 2\n|-\n|[[The Grizzly]]\n|1986\n|Wooden roller coaster\n|Modeled after the original [[Coney Island (Cincinnati)|Coney Island]] Wildcat. \n|bgcolor=\"#FF0000\" align=center | 4\n|-\n|[[Psycho Mouse]]\n|2001\n|[[Arrow Dynamics]]<br/>Wild Mouse roller coaster\n|The last Mad Mouse to be produced by Arrow Dynamics.\n|bgcolor=\"#FF0000\" align=center | 4\n|-\n|Thunder Raceway\n|2001\n|Go-kart track\n|Pay-per ride attraction.\n|bgcolor=\"#FF0000\" align=center | 4\n|-\n|Tiki Twirl\n|2006\n|[[Zamp